Key Principles for M&A Data Room Setup

Start early — Populate 70–80% of content before marketing begins (ideally 4–8 weeks pre-teaser). Incomplete rooms kill momentum.
Buyer-centric design — Mirror standard due diligence checklists and SPA disclosure schedules so buyers feel the seller is organized and transparent.
Clean & normalized data — Upload only final versions (avoid drafts unless requested); normalize financials for one-offs/EBITDA add-backs.
Naming & versioning — Consistent convention: e.g., 01_Corporate_Articles_of_Incorporation_v1.2_2025-12-15.pdf
Indexing — Use numbered/auto-indexed hierarchy (many VDRs offer this automatically) for easy navigation and reference in Q&A.
Security & access — Role-based permissions (e.g., tiered: teaser → CIM → full room); view-only for most; download/print controls; MFA, IP restrictions, watermarks.
Analytics — Track which folders/documents get the most views → signals buyer priorities or concerns.
Maintenance — Dedicated internal "data room captain" (often CFO + legal) + weekly updates; version control; Q&A log integration.

