Drawbacks & When to Stick with One-Factor

More parameters → harder calibration (optimization can be unstable; needs good initial guesses).
Still Gaussian → negative rates possible (mitigate with shifted Hull-White or switch to CIR-based if critical).
Overkill for short-horizon/mid-market M&A where rate risk is secondary to synergies/ops.

