Phased Synergies Concept (M&A / LBO Context)
In real deals, synergies are rarely realized instantly — they ramp up over time due to integration delays, cultural friction, system migrations, etc.
Typical phasing (adjustable):

Year 1: 20–40% of run-rate synergies
Year 2: 50–70%
Year 3: 80–90%
Year 4+: 100% (or slight fade if OU model used later)

We now randomize:

Total annual run-rate synergies (e.g., $15M base ± volatility)
Realization curve (beta distribution for each year’s % capture, skewed toward slower ramp-up)

This creates realistic variability in cash flow timing → directly impacts IRR distribution and probability of meeting hurdles.
