What "OU synergy fade" means in this context
Instead of using a fixed or deterministic ramp-up of synergies, we model the realized annual synergy level as a mean-reverting stochastic process (OU process):

Starts near the target run-rate synergy
Reverts toward a long-term sustainable level (usually lower, e.g. 60–80% of peak)
Has volatility around the path
This is very realistic for M&A: early wins → integration friction / cultural drag → stabilization at a lower level

Key parameters added

Initial synergy ≈ target run-rate
Long-term mean (θ) = fraction of target (e.g. 65–85%)
Reversion speed (κ) = how fast it pulls back (higher = faster fade)
Volatility (σ) = noise around the path

