Initial guess from OLS → helps convergence
Bounds prevent implausible values (negative κ or σ)
Returns approximate standard errors via Hessian inverse
Works well with daily data (dt=1/252); also fine with monthly/quarterly

Real-world usage tips (2026 context)

Data — Use effective federal funds rate (FRED: EFFR), ESTR, SONIA, or repo rates
Frequency — Daily is best; weekly/monthly also ok (adjust dt)
Sample length — 3–10 years (750–2500 daily points) gives good estimates
Market regime — Calibrate separately on different periods (pre- vs post-2022 hiking cycle)
Extensions — For time-dependent mean → Hull-White; for no negative rates → CIR

